To find the sum of the 8 neighbors of 2026 in the given spiral (starting with 1 at the center, going right then counterclockwise), first determine its grid position using the spiral's layer structure.

The spiral fills layers outward: layer 1 (numbers 1–8), layer 2 (9–25), etc. Layer \(k\) has side length \(2k-1\) and max number \((2k-1)^2\). For 2026, solve \((2k-1)^2 \geq 2026\): \(k = 23\) since \((45)^2 = 2025 < 2026 \leq (47)^2 = 2209\)[2].

2026 is on layer 23's bottom side (the 2nd number there, since 2025 + 1 = 2026). Relative to layer origin (23,23) in 1-indexed center-based coordinates, its position is (45, 24).

Convert to absolute 1-indexed row \(r=45\), column \(c=24\). The 8 neighbors' values are found using the CSES number spiral formula[2]:

| Direction | \(\Delta r\) | \(\Delta c\) | Position \((r', c')\) | Value |
|-----------|--------------|--------------|-----------------------|-------|
| Up        | -1           | 0            | (44,24)               | 2024 |
| Up-right  | -1           | 1            | (44,25)               | 2003 |
| Right     | 0            | 1            | (45,25)               | 2025 |
| Down-right| 1            | 1            | (46,25)               | 2208 |
| Down      | 1            | 0            | (46,24)               | 2207 |
| Down-left | 1            | -1           | (46,23)               | 2186 |
| Left      | 0            | -1           | (45,23)               | 2047 |
| Up-left   | -1           | -1           | (44,23)               | 2048 |

**Sum: 15936.**[2]

